Provides standard article footnotes for documenting the source of the inflated prices calculated by {{tlx|Inflation}}.

== Usage ==
  {{tlx|Inflation/fn}}
  {{tlx|Inflation/fn|''index''}}
  {{tlx|Inflation/fn|''index''|3=group=''groupname''}}

When the '''index''' parameter is provided, a footnote about that specific data set is generated. The index codes are the same as those used by {{tlx|Inflation}}:

* {{tlx|Inflation/fn|AU}} = {{Inflation/fn|AU}}
** {{tlx|Inflation/fn|AU-road}} = {{Inflation/fn|AU-road}}
* {{tlx|Inflation/fn|BD}} = {{Inflation/fn|BD}}
* {{tlx|Inflation/fn|CA}} = {{Inflation/fn|CA}}
* {{tlx|Inflation/fn|DE}} = {{Inflation/fn|DE}}
* {{tlx|Inflation/fn|IN}} = {{Inflation/fn|IN}}
* {{tlx|Inflation/fn|JP}} = {{Inflation/fn|JP}}
* {{tlx|Inflation/fn|KRW}} = {{Inflation/fn|KRW}}
* {{tlx|Inflation/fn|PH}} = {{Inflation/fn|PH}}
<!-- * {{tlx|Inflation/fn|TEST}} = {{Inflation/fn|TEST}} -->
* {{tlx|Inflation/fn|PK}} = {{Inflation/fn|PK}}
* {{tlx|Inflation/fn|UK}} = {{Inflation/fn|UK}}
** {{tlx|Inflation/fn|UK-GDP}} = {{Inflation/fn|UK-GDP}}
* {{tlx|Inflation/fn|US}} = {{Inflation/fn|US}}
** {{tlx|Inflation/fn|US-GDP}} = {{Inflation/fn|US-GDP}}
* {{tlx|Inflation/fn|ZAR}} = {{Inflation/fn|ZAR}}

When '''no''' <code>index</code> parameter is provided, or when an invalid index is provided, a generic footnote is generated with an error:

* {{tlx|Inflation/fn}} = {{Inflation/fn}}
* {{tlx|Inflation/fn|xyz}} = {{Inflation/fn|xyz}}

This is the reference list generated by the above examples:
{{reflist|33em}}

Anchor names produced are based on the index parameter, or its lack thereof. As a result, the same {{tlx|Inflation/fn|index}} code can be used many times in the same article while generating only one actual footnote per index code.

===Reference grouping===
If it is desired to place the footnote into a [[WP:REFGROUP|reference group]] other than the default, the {{para|group}} parameter may be used:

* {{tlx|Inflation/fn|UK|3=group=nb}} = {{Inflation/fn|UK|group=nb}}
{{reflist|group=nb}}

'''NB''' to group the footnote with other footnotes rather than references, ({{tl|notelist}}), use {{para|group|lower-alpha}}

See the [[Template:Inflation#Referencing|related section]] at {{tl|Inflation}} for additional instructions and examples.

===Date format===
Where the ''country'' is either <code>CA</code> or <code>US</code>, the generated reference includes the retrieval date of the data, which is shown in month-first (MDY) format. For <code>US</code> only, this may be altered to day-first (DMY) format by adding {{para|df|yes}}. This must be done each time the template is called in an article, or there will be an error message in the reference list.
* {{tlx|Inflation/fn|US|3=df=yes}} = {{Inflation/fn|US|df=yes}}
{{reflist|close=1}}

===Citation format===
The citations for several indexes use {{tl|cite web}} as a base template. This means the footnotes are output using [[Help:Citation Style 1|Citation Style 1]] (CS1) as a default. One (<code>IN</code>) uses {{tl|citation}} as a base template, resulting in [[Help:Citation Style 2|Citation Style 2]] (CS2) as a default. To switch between these, use {{para|mode|cs1}} or {{para|mode|cs2}} as appropriate. This must be done each time the template is called in an article, or there will be an error message in the reference list.
*{{tlx|Inflation/fn|US|3=mode=cs2}} = {{Inflation/fn|US|mode=cs2}}
*{{tlx|Inflation/fn|IN|3=mode=cs1}} = {{Inflation/fn|IN|mode=cs1}}
{{reflist|close=1}}

===Last author ampersands===
To promote consistency with an article that uses {{para|last-author-amp}} to join the last author in a list with an ampersand, footnotes that list multiple authors and the {{tl|cite web}} base template can also use this parameter. This must be done each time the template is called in an article, or there will be an error message in the reference list.
*{{tlx|Inflation/fn|US-GDP|3=last-author-amp=yes}} = {{Inflation/fn|US-GDP|last-author-amp=yes}}
{{reflist|}}

